OL,4,Cto the Kabul horror story
OL,6,FDisplaying a confidence we were not
OL,7,Ffeeling, we demanded "take us to your
OL,8,Fleader".
OL,10,FAt what had the day before been the UN
OL,11,Fheadquarters, we interviewed the man
OL,12,Fnow in charge of a large part of the
OL,13,FAfghan capital. A week before he was
OL,14,Frunning a suicide bomber school.
OL,16,FNever have I said 'sorry' so often.
OL,17,FEspecially to the women we met.
OL,19,FThese were people who had bet their
OL,20,Ffutures on us, only to see us cut and
OL,21,Frun.
