OL,6,FNear the entrance to the Baron Hotel
OL,7,Fthat day I noticed a family of four
OL,8,Fsitting in the shade of a wall.
OL,10,FI crouched down and asked the husband
OL,11,Fand father if he spoke English. He
OL,12,Fsaid he did and that he had worked as
OL,13,Fa terp (interpreter) for 42 Commando
OL,14,Fin Nad-e-Ali in Helmand Province.
OL,16,FThat struck a chord as I had embedded
OL,17,Fwith the Royal Marines in that exact
OL,18,Fplace.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
