OL,6,FThe man who had served UK forces told
OL,7,Fme he thought he had no chance of
OL,8,Fgetting away. He wasn't on any list.
OL,10,FThere were tears running down my
OL,11,Fcheeks as he told me this.
OL,12,FRidiculously, he started consoling me.
OL,14,FHe put an arm around me and said
OL,15,Frepeatedly, "It's ok, it's ok."
OL,17,FI'm thinking about that man and his
OL,18,Ffamily again today. Having abandoned
OL,19,Fthem four years ago, has governmental
OL,20,Fincompetence placed them in even more
OL,21,Fdanger?
